data.description: Listing agent: Kathy Potter, Call 800-221-6228 for information. This three bedroom, two and a half bath home is situated as the last home on a dead end street and it joins Ft Leonard Wood.  You will love the breath taking scenic views from your back deck.  This home offers the privacy you desire yet a quick 7-10 minutes commute to the front gates of Ft Leonard Wood.  The location allows you to go home for your shower after PT or for lunch.  This traditional two story home offers a great lay out with the open floor plan.  On the main floor you will love the hardwood entry to the main living area.  The large great room offers is adjacent to the kitchen/dining combo.  This open plan is great for real family living and for entertaining.  The kitchen and dining area style with easy care ceramic tile.  You will enjoy the almost new appliances and the staggered kitchen cabinetry.  There is also a pantry so you can stock up at the case load sells.  There is a convenient half bath on the main floor.  All three bedrooms are nestled on the second story of this home.  The two guest rooms share a common hall bath.  The master suite is located in the rear of the home.   The master bedroom is 16x14, and offers a spa like master bath including a jetted tub, separate shower, dual sink vanity. The basement area is completely unfinished at this time which allows for lots of storage or expansion for your family.  The basement area is plumbed for easy installation for the third full bath.  The first owner has certainly taken pride in ownership with this home and has installed some great landscaping.  The back yard offers a privacy fence.  You will love be kicked back sitting on your back deck sipping your favorite beverage and enjoying the beautiful Ozark evenings in this traditional two story home.
